  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b88\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc7 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba9 - \u0baa\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fares hiked to compensate Railway Department's losses - Bandula Gunawardena",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Railway Department is currently facing a loss of Rs 10 crore per day. Railway fares have been hiked to compensate for the loss.",
        "Minister Bandula Gunawardena said that in the midst of the current economic crisis, the Railway Department cannot be allowed to run at a loss.",
        "He made this known while announcing the weekly cabinet decisions held yesterday, Tuesday.",
        "Last year 2012, the monthly income of Railway Department was 4.8 billion rupees. But a loss of 34 billion rupees. Similarly, in 2021, the income is seen at 4.5 billion rupees, while the loss rises to 44 billion rupees.",
        "Due to the continued heavy losses, it has to face severe pressures in terms of payment of salaries to employees and payment to the petroleum corporation for procurement of fuel.",
        "Currently the Railway Department is facing a loss of Rs 10 crore per day. Only Rs 2.3 billion in overtime payments have been paid so far this year. Railway fares have been increased to meet such crises and to compensate for the loss.",
        "Currently, due to increase in fuel prices and problem in bus transport, most of the public has started traveling by train services. The number of train users has increased significantly compared to the last few months.",
        "However, no consideration has been given to increasing the number of coaches or increasing the number of trains.",
        "The reason is that due to non-payment of allowances for already imported railway coaches, the penalty is also due.",
        "He said that in the midst of such a situation, attention cannot be given to increasing the number of coaches."
      ],
